# Manual directory

`Manual/` is the user manual for WalkieTalkie, authored in [eBookED](https://github.com/JohnDovey/eBookED) via **`Manual/project.ebookproj.json`**. That JSON is the project file; open it in eBookED for spine order and exports. Prefer editing through eBookED when practical.

**Do not hand-edit `book.ebhtml` for structure** — it is auto-regenerated when the spine changes. Edit chapter content in `chapters/*.ebhtml` (or via the app). Keep `frontmatter/toc.ebhtml` aligned with the spine when chapters are added/renamed.

## Layout

- `project.ebookproj.json` — eBookED project (spine, metadata)
- `frontmatter/` — title page, TOC, copyright (bare HTML fragments, no `---` header)
- `chapters/` — topic chapters with `---` YAML header + HTML body
- `backmatter/` — notes, about, etc.
- `images/` — screenshots and figures
- `output/` — exported EPUB/PDF/DOCX (**committed**, not gitignored)
- `.eb-preview/` — local eBookED preview cache (**do not commit**)

## Topic chapters (required style)

**One topic per chapter** — do not dump the whole product into a single Getting Started file. Current spine pattern:

| Chapter (spine title) | Role |
|----------------------|------|
| Getting Started | Short intro only |
| The Base Station | Desktop dashboard, map, settings, tray, multi-BS, Remote Users, voice notes |
| MeshBridge | Dual-LAN / Ethernet / Wi‑Fi NIC / punch companion; not live Talk |
| Windows Builds / macOS builds | Platform packaging (incl. MeshBridge build scripts) |
| Android Client | Phone app usage and quirks |
| The iPhone app | iOS app usage and quirks |
| Wearables | Wear OS / Apple Watch |
| Notes (back matter) | Misc |

When a user-facing feature lands, update the **relevant topic chapter** (or add a new chapter via eBookED and the spine), not a catch-all.

Numbered filenames look like `NNN-Title.ebhtml`; spine **order** in `project.ebookproj.json` is authoritative if filenames are out of numeric order (eBookED may keep UUID-named stubs until renamed). Prefer descriptive titles in the chapter YAML `title:` field.

Chapter body header:

```
---
title: The Base Station
subtitle: Desktop
numberMode: Auto
numberOverride:
---
```

Then HTML sections (`<h1>`/`<h2>`, `<p>`, `<ul>`, `<pre><code>`, …).

## Images / figures (required style)

**Do not** insert bare `<p><img …></p>` for screenshots going forward.

Follow the Base Station chapter pattern — a centered `<figure>` with stable `id`, sized `<img>`, and `<figcaption class="caption">`:

```html
<figure id="fig:8a0d9d8458954e86aa0287c64c005f5f" style="text-align:center">
<img src="../images/base-station-dashboard.png" alt="base-station-dashboard" width="649" height="381">
<figcaption class="caption">Base Station Dashboard</figcaption>
</figure>
```

Rules:

- Paths are relative: `../images/filename.png`
- Prefer the figure+figcaption markup (eBookED inserts IDs; when hand-editing, keep an existing `fig:…` id or generate a new UUID-style id)
- Caption text is user-facing; `alt` can be a short slug matching the asset name
- Include `width` / `height` when known (as eBookED emits)
- Put the figure near the prose it illustrates; a short sentence after the figure is fine

## Before editing the Manual

**If `Manual/` differs from the last time you wrote to it, re-read the spine (`project.ebookproj.json` / `book.ebhtml`) and a recent topic chapter (especially The Base Station for figures) and match those patterns.** Do not reintroduce the old monolithic all-in-one chapter style or bare `<p><img>` screenshots.

## Build outputs

`Manual/output/` holds exported `.epub` / `.pdf` / `.docx` generated by the user — commit them when updated. Opposite of eBookED's own repo gitignore for `manual/output/`.
